snippets.snippet: It's an ideal base for exploring the Kansai region: Kyoto's World Heritage Sites, Nara's temple and Koya-san's eerie graves are within 90 minutes by train. Top city attractions include the aquarium, Osaka Castle, Universal Studios Japan and the futuristic Floating Garden Observatory.
snippets.title: Osaka Tourism 2020: Best of Osaka, Japan - Tripadvisor

snippets.snippet: Cafe HOLIDAY has as its concept Hawaiian breakfasts and lifestyle. I was pleasantly surprised at the huge fish tank, which makes the interior of the café look very fashionable. I went with a large party so we shared many delicious Hawaiian foods, from sweet to savory dishes.
snippets.title: “Cafe HOLIDAY”, a Hawaiian Café in Chayamachi, Umeda, Osaka

snippets.snippet: Osaka (大阪, Ōsaka) is Japan's second largest metropolitan area after Tokyo. It has been the economic powerhouse of the Kansai Region for many centuries. Osaka was formerly known as Naniwa. Before the Nara Period, when the capital used to be moved with the reign of each new emperor, Naniwa was once Japan's capital city, the first one ever known.
snippets.title: Osaka Travel Guide - What to do in Osaka

snippets.snippet: Tidligere Fuji Sushi Tønsberg har nå blitt Osaka Sushi Tønsberg med samme eier. Vi lager fortsatt den samme gode sushien til den samme lave prisen. Hvis du vil ha rask, rimelig og deilig sushi har du kommet til riktig sted! Du finner oss i Conradis gate, vis-a-vis biblioteket i sentrum.
snippets.title: Osaka Sushi Tønsberg

snippets.snippet: Traveling in Osaka with Children. If you’re coming to Japan with children or infants, you should strongly consider spending a few days in Osaka. Keep in mind that Kyoto is only 14 minutes away from Osaka by shinkansen (bullet train), so you can consider Kyoto to be almost a part of Osaka.
